# Documentation Maintenance Patterns

## Update Triggers
- **Pattern**: Update documentation when related code changes
- **Key**: Code changes, new features, bug fixes, configuration changes
- **Process**: Identify affected documentation, update content, verify accuracy
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#update-triggers)

## Content Validation
- **Pattern**: Verify all information is accurate and current
- **Key**: Test code examples, check links, validate procedures
- **Tools**: Automated checks, manual review, user testing
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#content-validation)

## Cross-Reference Management
- **Pattern**: Maintain consistent cross-references between documents
- **Key**: Update links when files move, verify all references work
- **Process**: Check internal links, validate external links, update broken references
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#cross-references)

## Quality Assurance
- **Pattern**: Regular documentation quality checks
- **Key**: Accuracy, completeness, clarity, consistency
- **Process**: Self-review, peer review, technical review, final review
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#quality-assurance)

## Version Control
- **Pattern**: Track documentation changes in git
- **Key**: Use feature branches, conventional commits, pull requests
- **Process**: Branch, edit, commit, review, merge
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#version-control)

## Review Process
- **Pattern**: Multi-stage review process for documentation changes
- **Key**: Self-review, peer review, technical review, final review
- **Process**: Plan, write, review, test, maintain
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#review-process)

## Maintenance Schedule
- **Pattern**: Regular documentation maintenance cycles
- **Key**: Monthly reviews, quarterly audits, release cycle updates
- **Process**: Identify outdated content, update information, verify accuracy
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#maintenance-schedule)

## Documentation Lifecycle
- **Pattern**: Plan, create, review, maintain, update, retire
- **Key**: Identify needs, write content, review quality, maintain currency
- **Process**: Planning, creation, review, maintenance, updates
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#documentation-lifecycle)

## Common Issues
- **Pattern**: Address common documentation problems
- **Key**: Outdated information, broken links, inconsistent formatting
- **Solutions**: Regular updates, link checking, style guidelines
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#common-documentation-issues)

## Success Metrics
- **Pattern**: Measure documentation quality and effectiveness
- **Key**: Accuracy, completeness, clarity, currency, usage
- **Metrics**: Quality scores, user feedback, access frequency
- **Reference**: [Documentation Guide](mdc:docs/DOCUMENTATION_GUIDE.md#success-metrics)
